!
!              NOTE 1: FOR THE TRUNCATED EXPONENTIAL, IF YOU SET
!                      MU1=MU2, A PPCC PLOT FOR SD ONLY IS GENERATED.
!
!              NOTE 2: THE NON-CENTRAL T, NON-CENTRAL CHI-SQUARE,
!                      SKEW T, INVERTED BETA, LOG-SKEW-NORMAL,
!                      GENERALIZED ASYMMETRIC LAPLACE,
!                      GENERALIZED MCLEISH, HYPERBOLIC
!                      HAVE EXPENSIVE PERCENT POINT FUNCTIONS, SO
!                      THE PPCC PLOT CAN TAKE A LONG TIME (SO MAY
!                      NOT BE PRACTICAL EXCEPT FOR RATHER SMALL DATA
!                      SETS).  WE ADDRESS THIS WITH THE COMMAND
!
!                         SET PPCC PLOT DATA POINTS <VALUE>
!
!                      IF THIS VALUE IS SET, THEN THE PPCC/KS
!                      PLOT WILL COMPUTE THAT NUMBER OF EQUALLY
!                      SPACED PERCENTILES OF THE DATA RATHER
!                      THAN THE RAW DATA.
